title: Desperate hunt for mother, 22, missing with her five-year-old child amid concerns for her welfare
text:
A desperate hunt is underway for a mother and daughter that have gone missing over night.

Sabrina Christiansen, 22, and her daughter, five, were last seen Friday around 6.30pm on Leitches Road in Brendale, 20km north of Brisbane.

Police are appealing for public assistance to help find the pair and hold concerns for their welfare as this disappearance is out of character.

Sabrina Christiansen (right), 22, and her daughter, 5 (left), were last seen Friday around 6.30pm on Leitches Road in Brendale, 20km north of Brisbane

Sabrina is described as Caucasian and approximately 169cm tall.

She has auburn hair and green eyes and was last seen wearing a dark blue shirt and shorts.

Anyone with information regarding their whereabouts are asked to contact police via Policelink on 131 444 or contact crime stoppers anonymously on 1800 333 000.
description: A desperate hunt is underway for a mother and daughter (pictured) that have gone missing overnight from Brendale, northern Brisbane.
authors: Tita Smith For Daily Mail Australia
